The Fitbit Versa smartwatch will be available in South Africa for an RRP of R3,199 from mid-April 2018. The Versa is Fitbit’s second wearable built on the Pebble software platform, and features Fitbit OS version 2.0. It is Fitbit’s lightest metal watch, and features three physical buttons on its sides and a 1.34-inch, 300 x 300 LCD touchscreen. It is water resistant up to 50m, has an optical heart-rate monitor, onboard storage, and on-device coaching with Fitbit Coach. Accessories for the Fitbit Versa will range from R499 to R1,499, said the company.  